The creep curves corresponding to Figure 6a only demonstrated both primary creep and steady-
state creep stages. As shown in Figure 6a, at 200 ps of the creep process, the atomic diffusion at the
grain boundary was obvious, and the shape of the crystal grain did not change significantly. The
creep curves corresponding to Figure 6b revealed a tertiary creep stage. As shown in Figure 6b, the
diffusion of the grain boundary occurred first in the model. At 40 ps of this simulation, the atoms at
the inner part of the grain were diffused, and the shape of the grain was elongated significantly. In
accordance with the creep curve, it was found that the tertiary creep stage is accompanied by the
